addToWhitelist(address[],uint16[]).details: Adds a batch of addresses with amounts to the whitelist.

params._addresses: The addresses to add to the whitelist.
params._amounts: The amounts the addresses are whitelisted for.

earned(uint256).details: Returns the amount of tokens an ID will yield on kill Killing an animal before it has reached maturity will result in a penalty burn.

params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query.

evolve(uint256,uint256).details: Each animal can be evolved two times. Evolving will increase the number of tokens the animal has and changes its visible features. Destroys  `tokenIdB` and evolve the `tokenIdA`, See {ERC721-_burn}.

params.tokenIdA: uint256 ID of the first animal.
params.tokenIdB: uint256 ID of the second animal.

grantWhitelistRole(address).details: Grant whitelist role to an address.

params._address: The address to grant the whitelist role to.

hatch(uint256,uint256,address).details: Hatching will mint their random animal once the VRF callback is done. Each animal holds a different amount of $DZOO tokens within it

params.amount: uint256 representing the amount of tokens to hach an egg.
params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the egg to be hatched.

initialize(string,string,address,bytes32.details: Initializes the contract by setting a `name` and a `symbol` to the ERC721 collection.See {ERC721}.

params._baseAnimals: is the address of the base animals contract.
params._govOperator: is the address of the governance operator.
params._ipfsHash: is the IPFS hash for the NFT pictures.
params._keyHash: is the keyHash for the VRF.
params._subId: is the subscription ID for the VRF.
params._totalSupply: is the total supply of NFTs.
params._vrfCoordinator: is the address of the VRF Coordinator.
params._whitelistMint: is the number of NFTs that can be minted by whitelisted addresses.

kill(uint256).details: Burns `tokenId`. See {ERC721-_burn}. The shorter the animal lives the more $DZoo will be released at burn. Killing an animal before it has reached maturity will result in a penalty burn.

params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be burned.

mint(address,uint256).details: Can only be called by the ZOO staking contract following the staking rules.

params.amount: uint256 representing the amount of eggs to be minted.
params.to: address representing the owner of the given token ID.

mintWhitelist(uint16).details: Can only be called by the whitelisted addresses.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeFromWhitelist(address[]).details: Removes a batch of addresses from the whitelist.

params._addresses: The addresses to remove from the whitelist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

revokeWhitelistRole(address).details: Revoke whitelist role from an address.

params._address: The address to revoke the whitelist role from.

setVRFParams(uint64,bytes32,uint16,uint3.details: Can only be called by the contract owner.

params._callbackGasLimit: uint32 representing the callback gas limit.
params._numWords: uint32 representing the number of random words to return.
params._requestConfirmations: uint16 representing the number of request confirmations.

setZooStaking(address).details: Can only be called by the contract owner.

params.dZooStaking_: address representing Degen Zoo Staking contract address.

setZooToken(address).details: Can only be called by the contract owner.

params._dZooToken: address representing Degen Zoo ERC20 contract address.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns an array of bytes representing the { Base64 } encoded version of the dataURI with the JSON data instructions. Since abi.encodePacked() can only take a maximum of 12 parameters, metadata assembly is split into multiple phases.

params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

MAX_SUPPLY().notice: MAX_SUPPLY is the maximum number of NFTs that can be minted.

animals(uint256).notice: Mapping from index to all animals parameters

evolve(uint256,uint256).notice: Users can evolve their Animals by feeding them a different animal.

hatch(uint256,uint256,address).notice: Users can hatch their Eggs by burning 4,000 $DZOO tokens to 40,000 $DZOO tokens

kill(uint256).notice: Burning the animal NFT releases the locked tokens within it based on the individual life expectancy ranging from 10 to 250 days.

metadata(uint256).notice: Mapping from token ID to NFT Metadata

mint(address,uint256).notice: Safely mints an Egg and transfers it to `to`.

mintWhitelist(uint16).notice: Safely mints an Egg and transfers it to _msgSender() .

setZooStaking(address).notice: Sets the Degen Zoo Staking contract address.

setZooToken(address).notice: Sets the Degen Zoo ERC20 contract address.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for `tokenId` token.

whitelistMintRemaining().notice: remanining amout of eggs that can be minted by whitelisted addresses.

zooRemainingToAssign().notice: zooRemainingToAssign is the number of Zoo tokens remaining to be assigned to NFTs.
